The floating debris seems to rise from small green slimy clumps in the sand beneath the water.  The debris were widely scattered when I recorded data around 8 this morning, but spread rapidly after that. By noon there was a fair amount of blue-green algae extending from shoreline to about 30 feet out in the lake. There has been a marked increase in the number of carp in the last couple of days. They may account for the increased murkiness of the water.  I only saw a few carp until two days ago, but 5 to 10 were visible the hour I paddleboarded after recording my data for the day.
